verbose_text: In addition, miR-122 positively regulates the p53 pathway via cyclin G1 [XREF_BIBR], miR-125b directly inhibits p53 [XREF_BIBR], and miR-21 negatively regulates the p53 pathway by targeting heterogeneous nuclear ribonucleoprotein K (HNPRK), a positive regulator of the p53 pathway, and the p53 homolog, p63 [XREF_BIBR].
